If you want to write.. I think something like sounds a little better. 

Handle hostname D-bus errors

Currently, hostname D-bus errors are not mapped to Redfish
errors, so a hostname patch returns an internal error irrespective of the D-bus error.

This commit handles the InvalidArgument D-bus error for the hostname.

Tested By:
Configure hostname with various invalid arguments
Done

This patch looks fine.  Is there a way we can abstract this out into all setProperty calls?  Basically every time we call SetProperty in redfish, we want to do this same operation (check for InvalidArgument, and translate to Redfish equivalent).

How difficult would that be to abstract in the future?
Nothing further than Ed's comment and question.
yeah I think we can abstract but each property may throw different set of d-bus errors, may be can try writing a standard/util method which can be used in setProperty

>  each property may throw different set of d-bus errors

Realistically they shouldn't be.  I realize in practice they might, but it's going to be a superset of dbus errors, and we could have one method that could handle the vast majority, right?
Yes, can be done
can we keep this method in utils which can be used across bmcweb?
handleHostnamePatchCallback
